---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "O Dividend Analysis & History",
  description: "Investigate 'The Monthly Dividend Company's' latest yield, historic 30+ year growth streak, and key property metrics. Is O right for you?",
  category: "tool",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "O Dividend Analysis & History",
    "description": meta.description,
    "datePublished": meta.published,
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Westmount Fundamentals"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the o dividend?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The O dividend is a monthly distribution paid by Realty Income Corporation (ticker: O), a prominent real estate investment trust (REIT) focused on single-tenant commercial properties."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the o dividend yield?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The current O dividend yield is approximately 5.02%, offering a competitive risk-adjusted return relative to both Treasury bonds and broader equity indexes."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the o dividend history?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "O has an exceptional dividend history, increasing its payout for over 31 consecutive years. Over the last five years, total annual payouts per share rose from roughly $2.32 in 2021 to $3.49 in 2025."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How frequently does Realty Income pay its dividend?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Realty Income explicitly brands itself as 'The Monthly Dividend Company' and pays its distribution consistently on a monthly basis."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is the O dividend safe?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Historically, O's dividend is considered highly safe due to its diversified portfolio of over 15,500 properties, triple-net lease structures, and consistently high occupancy rates."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<SiteLayout site="westmount" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://westmountfundamentals.com/o-dividend" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>O Dividend Analysis & History</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Exploring the payout resilience of 'The Monthly Dividend Company'</p>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2>Realty Income (O) Overview & Key Metrics</h2>
      <p><strong>Realty Income Corporation (O)</strong> is one of the most celebrated Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) on the market, uniquely known for its trademarked identity as "The Monthly Dividend Company." Its business model involves acquiring freestanding, single-tenant commercial properties in the United States and Europe, leasing them out on long-term triple-net agreements.</p>

      <p>Because it is a REIT, Realty Income is legally required to distribute at least 90% of its taxable income to shareholders. This structural mandate makes the <strong>o dividend</strong> a highly attractive, predictable source of monthly cash flow for income-focused investors.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Current Snapshot</h3>
        <table>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th>Current Dividend Yield</th>
              <td>5.02%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Price-to-Earnings (P/E) Ratio</th>
              <td>55.08 (Note: FFO is a better metric for REITs)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Market Capitalization</th>
              <td>$60.30 Billion</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <td>Real Estate</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th>Payout Frequency</th>
              <td>Monthly</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>The <strong>o dividend yield</strong> at roughly 5.02% sits comfortably above historical averages for the S&P 500, though as a real estate equity, it is notably sensitive to shifting macroeconomic interest rate environments.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>O Dividend History & Consistency</h2>
      <p>The core thesis for owning Realty Income revolves entirely around its formidable <strong>o dividend history</strong>. As an S&P 500 Dividend Aristocrat, Realty Income has raised its dividend for over 31 consecutive years, surviving dot-com busts, the Great Financial Crisis, and global pandemics without a single cut.</p>

      <div class="card">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Year</th>
              <th>Total Annual Payout (per share)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>2021</td>
              <td>$2.32</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2022</td>
              <td>$2.97</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2023</td>
              <td>$3.06</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2024</td>
              <td>$2.87 (Adjusted for spin-offs/specials)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>2025</td>
              <td>$3.49</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>Recent payouts in 2025 and early 2026 have stabilized at $0.27 per share per month. This methodical, quarter-cent quarterly increase allows investors to outpace baseline inflation while compounding their shares faster through monthly reinvestment.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Dividend Reinvestment (DRIP) Calculator</h2>
      <p>The true power of "The Monthly Dividend Company" lies in monthly compounding. Use the calculator below to model the effect of a DRIP utilizing O's monthly distribution frequency, assuming a static yield and price.</p>

      <div class="card calculator-container">
        <h3>Project Your O Income</h3>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label for="sharesInput" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; font-weight:bold;">Shares Owned:</label>
          <input type="number" id="sharesInput" value="100" min="1" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);">
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <label for="priceInput" style="display:block; margin-bottom:0.5rem; font-weight:bold;">Current Price per Share ($):</label>
          <input type="number" id="priceInput" value="65.00" step="0.01" style="width:100%; padding:0.75rem; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color); background:var(--bg-color); color:var(--text-primary);">
        </div>
        <button id="calcBtn" style="background:var(--accent-color); color:#fff; border:none; padding:0.75rem 1.5rem; border-radius:6px; font-weight:bold; cursor:pointer; width:100%;">Calculate Annual Income</button>

        <div id="calcResults" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; display:none; padding:1rem; background:var(--bg-color); border-radius:6px; border:1px solid var(--border-color);">
          <p style="margin:0 0 0.5rem 0;">Estimated Annual Income (No Reinvestment): <strong id="resNoDrip" style="color:var(--accent-color); font-size:1.2rem;">$0.00</strong></p>
          <p style="margin:0;">Estimated Annual Income (With DRIP): <strong id="resDrip" style="color:var(--accent-color); font-size:1.2rem;">$0.00</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:0.8rem; color:var(--text-secondary); margin-top:0.5rem;">*Assumes a static 5.02% yield and constant share price. DRIP compounds monthly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Comparison to Category Average</h2>
      <p>Compared to other Real Estate investment options, Realty Income is considered a premium-tier defensive play. While you might find higher raw yields in mortgage REITs or highly leveraged retail REITs, O offers unmatched safety due to its massive scale and focus on non-discretionary retail tenants (e.g., grocery stores, convenience stores, pharmacies). Compared to broad market income funds like <a href="/vym-dividend">VYM</a> or aggressive options funds like <a href="/ymax-dividend-history">YMAX</a>, Realty Income sits solidly in the "dependable growth" bucket—sacrificing explosive growth for nearly guaranteed monthly liquidity.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the o dividend?</summary>
        <p>The O dividend is a monthly distribution paid by Realty Income Corporation (ticker: O), a prominent real estate investment trust (REIT) focused on single-tenant commercial properties.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the o dividend yield?</summary>
        <p>The current O dividend yield is approximately 5.02%, offering a competitive risk-adjusted return relative to both Treasury bonds and broader equity indexes.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the o dividend history?</summary>
        <p>O has an exceptional dividend history, increasing its payout for over 31 consecutive years. Over the last five years, total annual payouts per share rose from roughly $2.32 in 2021 to $3.49 in 2025.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How frequently does Realty Income pay its dividend?</summary>
        <p>Realty Income explicitly brands itself as 'The Monthly Dividend Company' and pays its distribution consistently on a monthly basis.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is the O dividend safe?</summary>
        <p>Historically, O's dividend is considered highly safe due to its diversified portfolio of over 15,500 properties, triple-net lease structures, and consistently high occupancy rates.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const calcBtn = document.getElementById('calcBtn');
      if(calcBtn) {
        calcBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const shares = parseFloat(document.getElementById('sharesInput').value) || 0;
          const price = parseFloat(document.getElementById('priceInput').value) || 0;
          const yieldPct = 0.0502; // 5.02%

          const principal = shares * price;
          const incomeNoDrip = principal * yieldPct;

          // Simple monthly compounding approximation for DRIP
          const monthlyRate = yieldPct / 12;
          const finalValue = principal * Math.pow(1 + monthlyRate, 12);
          const incomeDrip = finalValue - principal;

          document.getElementById('resNoDrip').textContent = '$' + incomeNoDrip.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
          document.getElementById('resDrip').textContent = '$' + incomeDrip.toLocaleString(undefined, {minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2});
          document.getElementById('calcResults').style.display = 'block';
        });
      }
    });
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    /* NO :root block. Use CSS vars: --bg-color, --card-bg, --border-color, --accent-color, --text-primary, --text-secondary */
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    th, td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    th { font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.85rem; text-transform: uppercase; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    .calculator-container label { color: var(--text-primary); }
    a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
